        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What's a geo-grid scan?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A geo-grid is a checkerboard of points across your service area where the tool checks your Maps rank for one keyword. Instead of one rank number, you see a grid showing where you appear in the local pack and where you don't. It's the only honest way to measure local visibility." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "How long does it take to rank higher on Google Maps?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "30–60 days for visible geo-grid lift in low-competition cities. 90+ days in competitive metros like Los Angeles or New York. The biggest predictor is how consistent your posting, review, and citation activity is — not the tool you buy." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can I rank on Google Maps without a paid tool?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — post weekly in the free Google Business Profile dashboard, ask every customer for a review, fix NAP across major directories. The problem is consistency: most owners stop after week three. A paid autopilot tool exists because doing it manually fails predictably." }},
